Zelda, dear, I do believe

519
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,320
they're giving us a run
for our money.

520
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:21,480
You're the Fitzgeralds.

521
00:21:21,560 --> 00:21:22,600
And we pride ourselves

522
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,880
the most quarrelsome couple in Paris.

523
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,880
Don't worry. We're not a couple.

524
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:28,440
Well, the night is still young.

525
00:21:28,520 --> 00:21:29,960
You should join us for a drink.

526
00:21:30,040 --> 00:21:33,640
Besides, no one should be out
on the streets alone tonight.

527
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:36,400
There is a monster on the loose.

528
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:38,640
- You heard about the monster.
- Come with me.

529
00:21:38,720 --> 00:21:40,760
What conversation isn't better
had over a gin rickey?

530
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,240
Do you hear that?

531
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:06,840
Dalí's the only one
who's seen the beast.

532
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,040
Take it for what it's worth.

533
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:09,640
Well, I spoke with him myself,

534
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:12,880
and according to Dalí,
this is what it looks like.

535
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:15,720
I can never make heads
or tails of Salvador's work.

536
00:22:15,800 --> 00:22:16,800
That's a Minotaur.

537
00:22:17,520 --> 00:22:19,600
A beast-alf man, half bull,

538
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:21,320
spent its whole life
lost in a maze?

539
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:23,120
Oh, now, that's the common myth,

540
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,760
but I heard a different story.

541
00:22:24,840 --> 00:22:27,120
The Minotaur, he's not lost.

542
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:28,200
He's hiding.

543
00:22:28,880 --> 00:22:30,360
Rejected by his father,

544
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:32,160
he felt that he had no place
in the real world,

545
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:35,000
and so he chose to stay in the maze.

546
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:36,480
If Dalí thinks he's seen one of these

547
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:37,600
I want what he's drinking.

548
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:41,000
Where you going?

549
00:22:41,080 --> 00:22:42,360
I am going to figure out

550
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,520
a way to catch a Minotaur

551
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:44,640
and show my father

552
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:46,360
what a real man of action
looks like.

553
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,960
There it is, awaiting the fight.

554
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:52,560
I got this! Mine's longer.

555
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:17,160
- Fall back!
- Wait, I've got the shot.

556
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:20,520
We have to go now!

557
00:23:20,600 --> 00:23:21,680
I'll never surrender.

558
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:24,720
But I will strategically retreat.

559
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:26,480
Get back!

560
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:33,040
Gideon, Hank's hurt.
Show him what you can do.

561
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,240
<i>Right away, Captain.</i>

562
00:23:34,320 --> 00:23:35,960
Dad, are you okay?

563
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:37,680
Please don't blame the Legends.

564
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:38,760
I should have been there.

565
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:40,920
Because then you would have seen me
lock eyes with the beast,

566
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,840
and it was in that moment

567
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,480
that I felt a deep
and mutual respect.

568
00:23:45,560 --> 00:23:47,200
Wow, someone's been
bonding with Papa.

569
00:23:47,280 --> 00:23:49,080
- Yeah.
- Respect that gave way to resolve

570
00:23:49,160 --> 00:23:51,080
as the beast drew its blade.

571
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,520
The dance had begun.

572
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:55,080
- Okay, Gideon.
<i>- Initiating scan.</i>

573
00:23:55,160 --> 00:23:57,840
So Cliffs Notes
big ax, bigger monster,

574
00:23:57,920 --> 00:23:59,640
knows we're on it.
We need a plan B quick.

575
00:23:59,720 --> 00:24:01,640
Okay. Dad, you heal up.

576
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,360
- We've got this.
- No, like hell.

577
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:06,120
I owe it to him to finish
this... fight.

578
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:07,520
<i>Sedative administered.</i>

579
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,120
And you thought a Minotaur
was bullheaded?

580
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:11,200
Oh, mythology burn.

581
00:24:11,280 --> 00:24:12,600
It's good to have you back.

582
00:24:13,360 --> 00:24:14,840
There has to be a way out of here.

583
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,480
Well, it's a prison cell.

584
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:19,320
Or an incubator
for our burgeoning friendship.

585
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:21,080
Isn't breaking out of prison
your thing?

586
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:23,120
Only reason I escaped last time was

587
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:24,720
because Ray gave me a Time Stone.

588
00:24:24,800 --> 00:24:25,800
Tell me everything,

589
00:24:25,880 --> 00:24:27,880
because I am big-time shipping
you two.

590
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:30,400
No shipping the inmates.

591
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:32,200
It's the reason we're stuck
in here in the first place.

592
00:24:33,800 --> 00:24:36,800
I know that getting
your boss locked in a prison

593
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,960
isn't the best way to start a job,

594
00:24:39,040 --> 00:24:41,920
so if it comes to it,
I'd like you to eat me first.

595
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,440
No one's eating anyone, Mona,

596
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:45,600
but when we get out of here,
we do have to talk about

597
00:24:45,680 --> 00:24:47,360
your continued employment
at the Bureau.

598
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,520
Wait, no, no, no, you can't fire me.

599
00:24:50,600 --> 00:24:51,800
Give me one good reason why.

600
00:24:53,120 --> 00:24:54,440
Okay. Okay.

601
00:24:57,600 --> 00:25:01,160
I was gonna save
this for upstairs, but...

602
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,720
surprise!

603
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:09,000
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

604
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:11,480
<i>Happy birthday to...</i>

605
00:25:11,560 --> 00:25:13,720
This isn't making
things better, is it?

606
00:25:13,800 --> 00:25:15,400
No, it's fantastic. Keep going.

607
00:25:16,480 --> 00:25:17,480
So, that's it?

608
00:25:17,560 --> 00:25:20,560
I finally find a job
where I can use my skills...

609
00:25:20,640 --> 00:25:21,640
Debatable.

610
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:25,200
And I blow it in the first week.

611
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:28,320
Guess I'm stuck
doing my fallback plan,

612
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,000
going back to law school.

613
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:31,480
At least, Yale wants me.

614
00:25:32,600 --> 00:25:34,480
Wait, wait, that's the fallback plan?

615
00:25:34,560 --> 00:25:37,680
Law school?
What are you even doing here?

616
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:39,520
This is my dream job.

617
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,600
It's my mom who wants me
to be a lawyer.

618
00:25:41,680 --> 00:25:44,560
No, you can't give in
to what your parents want.

619
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:47,400
That's what I did,
and look how that ended.

620
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:49,840
Okay, you're not gonna take

621
00:25:49,920 --> 00:25:51,640
life advice from Nora Dhark, right?

622
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:53,920
That's rich.
You should listen to your parents.

623
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,000
Think about your future.

624
00:25:55,080 --> 00:25:57,640
Oh, easy for you to say.
At least, you had a future.

625
00:25:57,720 --> 00:25:59,240
When I was a kid, my dad convinced me

626
00:25:59,320 --> 00:26:00,440
to be a demon vessel.

627
00:26:00,520 --> 00:26:01,840
You think it was easy for me?

628
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:02,960
At least, you got to be a kid.

629
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:05,040
Try being a clone from 2213, okay?

630
00:26:05,120 --> 00:26:06,760
The only taste of childhood
I've ever had

631
00:26:06,840 --> 00:26:08,760
was almost being killed
by a Shtriga at summer camp.

632
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,960
Wow, okay, I need to hear

633
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:12,800
your entire life stories right now.

634
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:13,960
No.

635
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,280
We might as well
get to know each other

636
00:26:15,360 --> 00:26:16,440
if we're stuck here.

637
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:18,000
Or...

638
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:20,280
at least have a drink?

639
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:22,920
Where did you...

640
00:26:24,080 --> 00:26:26,080
We need to bag ourselves a Minotaur

641
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:28,040
before your dad gets himself killed.

642
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:29,640
Oh, what is that smell?

643
00:26:29,720 --> 00:26:31,240
Did you guys get a team dog
without me?

644
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:32,720
Because that was my idea.

645
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:33,840
Bet you guys are having

646
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:36,160
post-mission pizza parties now too.

647
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:40,120
This is the artificial musk
of a female Minotaur.

648
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:41,960
See, Minotaurs have
a very sharp sense of smell

649
00:26:42,040 --> 00:26:43,040
when it comes to tracking prey,

650
00:26:43,120 --> 00:26:44,320
but with this little bad boy,

651
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:47,360
I can lure it in by convincing
it that I'm a potential mate.

652
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,440
Then what?

653
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:49,600
You two gonna ride off together,

654
00:26:49,680 --> 00:26:50,960
get a nice little flat in Soho?

655
00:26:51,040 --> 00:26:52,800
It's good, but we still need
a way to tame it

656
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:53,880
and get it to the Bureau.

657
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,120
Taming the beast. Taming the beast.

658
00:26:56,200 --> 00:26:57,520
I read about this. I read about this.

659
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:01,560
Let's see,
"The Magical Treatise of Solomon."

660
00:27:02,280 --> 00:27:03,280
Here we go.

661
00:27:03,360 --> 00:27:04,840
"To ease the Minotaur's rage,

662
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:06,680
"his mother would play him a lullaby

663
00:27:06,760 --> 00:27:09,400
on a lute built by Daedalus."

664
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:10,480
That's it.

665
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:12,480
We'll lure it out
and lull it to sleep.

666
00:27:12,560 --> 00:27:14,880
No one gets hurt,
not even the Minotaur.

667
00:27:15,840 --> 00:27:17,440
And then we'll have a pizza party.

668
00:27:19,080 --> 00:27:20,080
And that's when I found out

669
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:21,160
I was from the future.

670
00:27:21,240 --> 00:27:23,280
- Whoa, the future.
- Yep.

671
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:24,360
It was all fake

672
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:27,360
my parents, my memories,

673
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:28,680
growing up in Fresno.

674
00:27:28,760 --> 00:27:30,200
Still better than
spending your childhood

675
00:27:30,280 --> 00:27:32,120
with The Order
of the Shrouded Compass.

676
00:27:32,200 --> 00:27:34,400
Is that like the Sisterhood
of Traveling Pants?

677
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:36,840
Even worse. Death cult.

678
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:39,680
And before that,
I just moved around

679
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:41,680
from one mental institution
to the next.

680
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:44,960
Point is, you're lucky.

681
00:27:45,040 --> 00:27:46,080
I'm lucky?

682
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:48,000
I just wish my past was made up.

683
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,240
What, so you can wake up one day

684
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,960
and realize that you don't
have any family, friends,

685
00:27:51,040 --> 00:27:53,520
or life experiences to hold on to?

686
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:55,080
Doesn't sound that different

687
00:27:55,160 --> 00:27:56,640
from waking up in a prison cell.

688
00:27:57,440 --> 00:27:58,480
<i>Touché.</i>

689
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,600
Are you two kidding me right now?

690
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:06,000
Ava, you're a clone from the future,

691
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:09,160
and you run the Time Travel Bureau.

692
00:28:09,240 --> 00:28:10,920
And you're a witch.

693
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:14,320
And you escaped a cult

694
00:28:14,400 --> 00:28:16,640
and a real-life demon.

695
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:17,880
I did.

696
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:20,560
You two are, like,
the two coolest women

697
00:28:20,640 --> 00:28:22,320
I have ever met,

698
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:25,160
and I once met Gillian Anderson

699
00:28:25,240 --> 00:28:27,240
at an "X-Files" meet and greet.

700
00:28:27,920 --> 00:28:30,720
Wow. Mona, you are a gem.

701
00:28:30,800 --> 00:28:32,960
You know, we can't have a birthday

702
00:28:33,040 --> 00:28:34,320
without birthday cake.

703
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:35,480
Yeah!

704
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,480
Back on your feet already, Hank.

705
00:28:37,560 --> 00:28:39,000
Yeah, your gal patched me up good.

706
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:40,480
I'm just running
through our strategy.

707
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:42,560
Oh, wait, you let him use
our "D&D" miniatures?

708
00:28:42,640 --> 00:28:44,000
No, I didn't let him touch Cyndra,

709
00:28:44,080 --> 00:28:45,120
Lord of the Dark Elves.

710
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:46,720
You guys "D&D" without me too?

711
00:28:46,800 --> 00:28:49,080
Son, why are you holding
a tiny guitar,

712
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:50,520
or do I even want to know?

713
00:28:50,600 --> 00:28:52,040
Oh, this... this is a lute.

714
00:28:53,080 --> 00:28:54,080
Someone say loot?

715
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,960
This is what we're gonna use
to put the Minotaur to sleep.

716
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:57,240
I thought you said that was loot.

717
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:58,320
I don't understand.

718
00:28:58,400 --> 00:28:59,840
Well, I suppose it is more of a lyre.

719
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:00,960
Everyone's a liar.

720
00:29:01,040 --> 00:29:02,800
This is how we're gonna catch
our creature, Dad.

721
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:04,320
- That's your plan?
- Yeah.

722
00:29:04,400 --> 00:29:05,760
We're facing a literal monster.

723
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:07,680
You think you can destroy it
with a lute?

724
00:29:07,760 --> 00:29:08,920
Well, in the hands of a master,

725
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:11,560
a lute is a formidable weapon.
Just look at Sting, mate.

726
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:13,640
<i>Sorry to interrupt, but there's
a change in the timeline.</i>

727
00:29:13,720 --> 00:29:15,760
<i>An attack at Cafe du Dome
is imminent.</i>

728
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:16,920
<i>There will be no survivors.</i>

729
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:19,240
The Minotaur must be
tracking Hemingway's scent.

730
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:20,320
Let's move out.

731
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:22,880
Nathaniel, get out of my way.

732
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:25,240
I don't have to do
what you say anymore, Hank.

733
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:27,320
Really? Because as your superior,

734
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:29,480
I'm telling you to stand down.

735
00:29:29,560 --> 00:29:30,840
You're going for
the superior thing again?

736
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:33,320
You know, you don't want to
listen to me or understand me.

737
00:29:33,400 --> 00:29:36,960
You just... you just
want to be better than me.

738
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:39,440
Well, you're one
to talk about listening.

739
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:42,080
You've ignored every lesson
I've ever tried to teach you.

740
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:44,920
Because it's the same lesson
over and over again.

741
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,040
You want me to be
more like you, Hank.

742
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:49,080
But guess what. I'm not like you.

743
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:51,840
I don't like televised golf
or Tom Clancy books

744
00:29:51,920 --> 00:29:54,240
or '70s folk rock.

745
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:55,840
I don't know if you happened
to notice,

746
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,600
but I'm a grown-ass superhero...

747
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:02,960
who's just trying to play
the lute for a Minotaur.

748
00:30:04,320 --> 00:30:06,960
Fine, don't want to listen
to your old man?

749
00:30:07,040 --> 00:30:08,880
Maybe you'll listen to your captain.

750
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,680
I'm sorry, but I'm with Nate.

751
00:30:14,440 --> 00:30:16,920
I know his idea sounds crazy,
but he's right.

752
00:30:17,600 --> 00:30:18,800
That's what makes him a Legend,

753
00:30:19,560 --> 00:30:20,640
no matter where he is.

754
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:24,480
Look, you said you wanted
to see a Legends mission.

755
00:30:24,560 --> 00:30:25,600
Well, you're about to,

756
00:30:26,440 --> 00:30:28,680
and if it goes wrong, well,

757
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:30,320
you go ahead and fire all of us.

758
00:30:37,200 --> 00:30:39,240
The beast advanced.

759
00:30:39,320 --> 00:30:41,360
I turned on him, gun raised.

760
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:43,840
Seeing we'd reached an agreement,

761
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:45,160
- I fired!
- Oh!

762
00:30:45,960 --> 00:30:48,480
So, I don't think we'll be seeing
that creature anytime soon.

763
00:30:48,560 --> 00:30:49,560
And what is that?

764
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:55,120
Back for another go, are you?

765
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,640
Oi, fuzz ball, come on.

766
00:30:58,720 --> 00:31:01,040
Have a nice little whiff
of this, will you?

767
00:31:03,760 --> 00:31:05,000
That's your cue.

768
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:06,320
Okay.

769
00:31:06,400 --> 00:31:08,080
I haven't had much time
to rehearse, but...

770
00:31:18,920 --> 00:31:20,640
Now we end this.

771
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:21,720
No!

772
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:24,440
I warn you, I will strike a woman.

773
00:31:26,680 --> 00:31:28,840
That's for being on my summer
eighth grade reading list.

774
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:31,280
Oh, guys?

775
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:34,240
Nathaniel!

776
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:39,080
Always preferred Faulkner.

