800
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:46,480
I really should...

801
00:32:46,560 --> 00:32:49,680
Open it. Open it. Open it.

802
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:50,760
You know what?

803
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:55,360
Oh, hi there.

804
00:32:56,920 --> 00:32:58,720
- Ray?
- Yeah, hi.

805
00:32:58,800 --> 00:33:01,280
Oh, could I get some help?
I'm a little stuck.

806
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:13,000
- Get behind the bar!
- Good idea.

807
00:33:17,600 --> 00:33:18,760
I meant for cover.

808
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:20,720
Well, I like your version.

809
00:33:25,280 --> 00:33:27,720
See, it looks just as I drew it.

810
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:30,680
You leave that weirdo alone!

811
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:32,000
Your fight is with me!

812
00:33:34,760 --> 00:33:35,760
Toro!

813
00:33:38,120 --> 00:33:39,120
Come on.

814
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:41,280
Now the dance begins.

815
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:45,120
I needed to make sure
she was okay.

816
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:46,880
I wanted to make sure you were okay.

817
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:49,240
Actually, I just really wanted
to see her... you.

818
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:51,280
And then I thought I'd deliver
the message myself,

819
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:53,280
but then I got stuck in the glue.

820
00:33:53,840 --> 00:33:55,040
That was sweet.

821
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:57,720
Stupid but sweet.

822
00:33:57,800 --> 00:33:59,880
No, it's unacceptable

823
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:03,200
but, in this case,
clearly convenient.

824
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:05,720
So since you are so good
at getting people out of prison,

825
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:07,760
let's get the hell out of here,
shall we?

826
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:09,600
Yeah.

827
00:34:11,680 --> 00:34:13,440
Let's just hope the team
wasn't missing their QB.

828
00:34:16,720 --> 00:34:17,880
That's my boy!

829
00:34:25,520 --> 00:34:26,520
Over here!

830
00:34:30,400 --> 00:34:32,440
<i>There is a young cowboy</i>

831
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,720
<i>He lives on the range</i>

832
00:34:36,280 --> 00:34:38,280
<i>His horse and his cattle</i>

833
00:34:38,360 --> 00:34:40,840
<i>Are his only companions</i>

834
00:34:42,240 --> 00:34:44,440
<i>He works in the saddle</i>

835
00:34:44,520 --> 00:34:46,880
<i>And he sleeps in the canyons</i>

836
00:34:46,960 --> 00:34:49,160
<i>Waiting for summer</i>

837
00:34:49,240 --> 00:34:51,120
<i>His pastures to change</i>

838
00:34:51,200 --> 00:34:52,760
What is happening?

839
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:54,760
James Taylor, and it's good.

840
00:34:55,400 --> 00:34:57,240
<i>And as the moon rises</i>

841
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:59,280
<i>He sits by his fire</i>

842
00:34:59,960 --> 00:35:01,800
<i>Thinking about women</i>

843
00:35:01,880 --> 00:35:03,960
<i>And glasses of beer</i>

844
00:35:04,600 --> 00:35:06,280
<i>And closing his eyes</i>

845
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:08,720
<i>As the doggies retire</i>

846
00:35:09,320 --> 00:35:12,320
<i>He sings out a song which is soft</i>

847
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,880
<i>But it's clear</i>

848
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:17,120
<i>As if maybe someone could hear</i>

849
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:19,000
You got this, Dad.

850
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:25,040
<i>Good night, you moonlight ladies</i>

851
00:35:25,680 --> 00:35:28,760
<i>Rockabye, sweet baby James</i>

852
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:32,040
<i>Deep greens and blues</i>

853
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:34,640
<i>Are the colors I choose</i>

854
00:35:34,720 --> 00:35:38,400
<i>Won't you let me go down in my dreams</i>

855
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:43,840
<i>And rockabye, sweet baby James</i>

856
00:35:50,400 --> 00:35:53,320
Now, that is how you finish
a Legends mission.

857
00:35:54,240 --> 00:35:55,600
You did good, son.

858
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:56,960
Right back at you, Dad.

859
00:35:58,320 --> 00:35:59,640
I learned it from you, Nathaniel.

860
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:11,480
- Hola, Chupi!
- Hola!

861
00:36:11,560 --> 00:36:13,760
- Privet, Baba Yaga.
- Privet.

862
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:16,760
What's up, Nora?

863
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,800
Thought you were headed to Yale.

864
00:36:19,880 --> 00:36:21,600
After last night, I marched home

865
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:23,800
and told my parents
I didn't want to be a lawyer.

866
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:26,120
And also that I was craving nachos

867
00:36:26,200 --> 00:36:27,760
and wanted to do karaoke.

868
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,840
The rosé had really kicked
in at that point.

869
00:36:30,640 --> 00:36:33,360
Oh, and here,
my mom's homemade congee.

870
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,960
Great hangover cure.

871
00:36:38,560 --> 00:36:40,480
Hey, can you do me a favor?

872
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:42,800
I wrote...

873
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:45,000
I wrote Ray a letter.

874
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:48,920
It'd be an honor to deliver it.

875
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:52,360
Yeah, anything for my
generation's Ross and Rachel.

876
00:36:59,640 --> 00:37:01,760
Oh, morning, Director Sharpe.

877
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:03,920
A word, Mona.

878
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:06,760
What?

879
00:37:07,360 --> 00:37:09,520
Wait, are you firing me this time?

880
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:10,600
No, Mona.

881
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:12,560
After yesterday, I realized...

882
00:37:13,920 --> 00:37:16,080
there is some room for a little
humanity in this place.

883
00:37:19,960 --> 00:37:21,800
Aloha, Kaupe.

884
00:37:21,880 --> 00:37:23,760
Permission to scratch his tummy?

885
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:26,840
Permission granted.

886
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:30,760
And you should deliver that letter.

887
00:37:33,960 --> 00:37:36,840
Well, that was a chaotic,

888
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:39,520
reckless, wasteful mess.

889
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:41,400
I think I finally see
the value in the Legends.

890
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:43,120
Yeah, you could have led
with that last part.

891
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:44,440
We're glad to have you on board.

892
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:47,720
Well, this has been fun,

893
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:49,600
but it's time for me to get back.

894
00:37:49,680 --> 00:37:52,440
Yeah, you know what? I'll...

895
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,680
I'll meet you back there, Dad.

896
00:37:58,440 --> 00:38:00,400
He's right. This was fun.

897
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:02,160
It's good to be back.

898
00:38:02,240 --> 00:38:04,160
Well, the door is always open.

899
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:05,800
You know, coming back here,

900
00:38:05,880 --> 00:38:07,120
I thought it'd be like the old days,

901
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:08,840
but I don't know
what's more surprising,

902
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:10,960
the fact that so much has changed

903
00:38:11,040 --> 00:38:15,040
or at some point,
this became the old days.

904
00:38:15,120 --> 00:38:16,800
You'd think we of all people
would understand

905
00:38:16,880 --> 00:38:18,920
- that time makes no sense.
- Yeah.

906
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:22,000
But I guess it's something
you never accept.

907
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:23,960
You know I love you guys, right?

908
00:38:25,320 --> 00:38:26,320
But...

909
00:38:27,240 --> 00:38:28,480
I belong over there.

910
00:38:28,720 --> 00:38:29,720
I get it.

911
00:38:31,680 --> 00:38:32,680
I'm proud of you.

912
00:38:34,280 --> 00:38:38,000
So go on. Go do your adult thing,
and we'll see you around.

913
00:38:38,080 --> 00:38:39,080
Okay.

914
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:44,080
Though if you're not in a rush...

915
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,680
It's a pizza party.

916
00:38:47,760 --> 00:38:49,720
Yeah, here he is.

917
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:52,280
- Hey!
- Welcome back, ugly.

918
00:38:52,360 --> 00:38:54,280
Yes, what other bright ideas
are you gonna leave us with

919
00:38:54,360 --> 00:38:56,400
before you bugger off?

920
00:38:56,480 --> 00:38:57,480
Softball team.

921
00:38:57,560 --> 00:38:59,000
Oh, no, only electronic sports.

922
00:38:59,080 --> 00:39:00,160
Piñata Fridays.

923
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:02,240
How many times do I have
to say no to that?

924
00:39:02,920 --> 00:39:04,080
Unionizing.

925
00:39:04,160 --> 00:39:06,360
Oh, don't let Hank hear you say that.

926
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:08,440
You know, it's still weird
not having you around.

927
00:39:09,240 --> 00:39:11,040
Oh, man, I'll always be
right there, big guy,

928
00:39:11,120 --> 00:39:12,560
in that giant heart of yours.

929
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:15,000
And I'll be at the Bureau,

930
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:16,840
so you guys can literally
stop by whenever you want.

931
00:39:18,680 --> 00:39:20,440
But, you know, before I go,

932
00:39:20,520 --> 00:39:21,520
I do want to say one thing.

933
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:24,120
When I first stepped onto this ship,

934
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:27,600
I was, you know, trying to get away
from all my baggage back home,

935
00:39:27,680 --> 00:39:29,480
and I can't believe
I'm gonna say this,

936
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:31,720
Hemingway once wrote,

937
00:39:31,800 --> 00:39:33,080
"Can't get away from yourself

938
00:39:33,160 --> 00:39:34,960
by moving from one place to another."

939
00:39:35,760 --> 00:39:36,760
And thanks to you guys,

940
00:39:36,840 --> 00:39:37,960
I don't have to run anymore.

941
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:40,360
Being here with you all has turned me
into the man I need to be,

942
00:39:40,440 --> 00:39:43,000
and this place is special.

943
00:39:44,520 --> 00:39:46,200
And you never know
when it's gonna be over.

944
00:39:46,280 --> 00:39:48,800
So I say, Legends,

945
00:39:49,640 --> 00:39:51,000
enjoy the ride while it lasts.

946
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:52,080
Hear, hear.

947
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:53,320
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

948
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:55,000
- Cheers.
- Cheers, cheers, cheers.

949
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:58,400
Oh, you'll find your place here.

950
00:39:59,000 --> 00:40:00,000
I know I did.

